# Flutter Gen AI Chat UI Changes Log

## [2.0.2] - 2023-03-15

### Changed
- Made send button always visible by default at the package level
- Completely removed the `alwaysShowSend` property as it's now redundant
- Modified default input behavior to prevent focus issues when typing
- Updated documentation to reflect the new send button behavior

## [2.0.0] - 2023-06-10

### Breaking Changes
- Overhauled API to align more closely with Dila patterns
- Moved from centralized `AiChatConfig` to direct parameters in `AiChatWidget`
- Streamlined redundant and deprecated properties
- Reorganized configuration classes for better usability

### Improvements
- Enhanced documentation with comprehensive usage guide
- Added detailed migration guide from 1.x to 2.0
- Better IDE autocompletion support
- More intuitive parameter naming
- Cleaner code organization
- Simplified configuration objects

### Backward Compatibility
- Added `@Deprecated` markers to guide migration
- Maintained core functionality while improving API
- Preserved configuration objects but made them more focused

## [0.3.0] - 2023-07-11

### Added
- [FEATURE] [INPUT] Added comprehensive size control to InputOptions:
  - inputHeight - Explicit height control for text input field
  - inputContainerHeight - Height control for entire input container
  - inputContainerConstraints - Advanced size control with BoxConstraints
  - inputContainerWidth - Enum to control width behavior (fullWidth, wrapContent, custom)
- [DOC] [INPUT] Updated input_customization.md with documentation for all new sizing options
- [DOC] [INPUT] Added example code showing how to use the new size control features

## [0.2.0] - 2023-07-10

### Added
- [FEATURE] [INPUT] Added material customization properties to InputOptions:
  - materialElevation - Controls shadow depth of input container
  - materialColor - Controls background color of input container
  - materialPadding - Controls padding around input container

## [2.1.2] - 2024-07-10
### Added
- Added `ChatAction` model and `ChatActionsBar` widget for dynamic bottom action bar support
- Exposed `actionsBarConfig` in `ChatInput`
- Scaffoled integration hook in `AiChatWidget` 

## [2.1.3] - 2024-07-12
### Added
- Added tests for `scrollToFirstResponseMessage` feature to ensure proper functionality
- Updated documentation to explain scroll behavior control and best practices
- Fixed a bug where scroll controller wasn't properly attached in test environment 

## [2.1.4] - 2024-07-17
### Fixed
- Completely rewired the scroll behavior system for much higher reliability
- Added direct force scrolling methods for precise positioning in response chains
- Fixed scroll behavior in the example app with clearer visual indicators
- Added response chain recognition through 'responseId' custom property
- Improved testing features with more reliable scroll position maintenance
- Extended documentation with clearer instructions for implementing scrollToFirstResponseMessage
- Added debounce mechanism to prevent scroll jitter and flickering in onNewMessage mode
- Implemented smoother animations with longer durations for onNewMessage scroll behavior
- Fixed race conditions in scroll timing for multi-part response chains 
- Added convenient animation curve presets: smooth, bouncy, fast, decelerate, accelerate
- Enhanced example app to demonstrate different animation curve styles

## [2.1.5] - 2024-07-18
### Fixed
- Enhanced scrollToFirstResponseMessage feature to work with multi-part response chains
- Added response chain recognition through 'responseId' custom property
- Fixed scroll behavior in examples to properly show the beginning of AI responses
- Updated documentation to explain required properties for proper scrolling behavior
- Fixed property preservation during streaming updates 